               <p>Prisoner's Defence. In 1810 I married Sarah Harding, and for some years she continued as good a wife as ever man had - I do not believe any person could love a woman dearer - but she turned out every thing that was base, and has had children by other men. As she would not live with me any longer, I was obliged to do without her.</p>
               <p>GUILTY.</p>
